organizations.name: brief-maryland ag says state reached settlement with computer sciences corp

text:
February 9, 2018 / 9:22 PM / in 31 minutes BRIEF-Maryland AG Says State Reached Settlement With Computer Sciences Corp Reuters Staff 1 Min Read 
Feb 9 (Reuters) - Maryland Attorney General: 
* MARYLAND ATTORNEY GENERAL SAYS STATE REACHED SETTLEMENT WITH COMPUTER SCIENCES CORP TO RESOLVE LITIGATION BETWEEN CSC AND THE STATE 
* MARYLAND ATTORNEY GENERAL - SETTLEMENT RESOLVES DISPUTES FROM AN IT CONTRACT BETWEEN MARYLAND DEPARTMENT OF HEALTH, CSC 
* CSC TO PAY THE STATE $81 MILLION Further company coverage:
